Ferro Corp., Cleveland, expects to earn $12 million on sales of $271 million in the third quarter.
It earned $11.8 million on sales of $247 million a year earlier. 

The maker of industrial and chemical materials will post earnings of 52 cents a primary share, down from 56 cents a year earlier, after adjustment for dividends on convertible preferred stock issued in April 1988. 

For the nine months, Ferro expects to earn $37.6 million on sales of $818 million, compared with $34.9 million on sales of $748 million a year earlier.
The company estimated earnings at $1.70 a primary share, also after the effect of the dividend payable on preferred shares, compared with $1.69 in the year-earlier period. 

